# moblies-shop — Project Rules

**Last updated:** 2026-06-22

Always follow these rules for moblies-shop.

---

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 16 App Router (standalone Docker output)
- TypeScript (strict)
- PostgreSQL 16 + Prisma 6
- Auth.js Credentials + JWT session + bcryptjs (12 rounds)
- Tailwind CSS 4 + Radix UI (Shadcn-style in `components/ui/`)
- next-intl — Arabic (default, RTL) + English
- @react-pdf/renderer for A4 invoices (Noto Sans Arabic font)
- Vitest for unit tests
- Zod validation in `lib/validations/`

---

## Architecture

- **Single shop per deployment** — NOT multi-tenant
- Clean Architecture:
  - `lib/domain/` — errors, profit helpers, types
  - `lib/application/services/` — business logic
  - `app/(dashboard)/*/actions.ts` — thin server actions
- Monolith Next.js — no separate backend
- Server actions for mutations; API routes for auth, invoice PDF, backup, search
- Action results: `{ success: true; id?: string } | { error: string }`
- Server actions to client: use `.bind(null, id)` — never inline arrow from RSC

---

## Auth & Roles

### Prisma enum `Role`
`ADMIN` | `ACCOUNTANT` | `SALES` | `EMPLOYEE` (legacy → treated as SALES)

### Normalized roles (`lib/permissions.ts`)
| Role | Access |
|------|--------|
| **ADMIN** | Full access + users + settings + backup + profit reports |
| **ACCOUNTANT** | + purchases + expenses + cost price edit + financial reports |
| **SALES** / **EMPLOYEE** | POS, sales, inventory (no cost price), customers, repairs, programming, basic reports |

### Session helpers
- `requireUser()` — all authenticated routes
- `requireAdmin()` — `/users`, `/settings`
- `requireAccountantOrAdmin()` — `/purchases`, `/expenses`

### Middleware (`middleware.ts`)
- Admin only: `/users`, `/settings`
- Accountant or Admin: `/purchases`, `/expenses`

### Bootstrap admin from `.env`
`ADMIN_EMAIL`, `ADMIN_PASSWORD`, `ADMIN_NAME`, `ADMIN_LOCALE`

---

## Database (Prisma)

### Key models
User, ShopSettings, Warehouse, Category, Product, Sale, SaleItem, Purchase, PurchaseItem, SaleReturn, PurchaseReturn, Expense, Customer, Payment, StockTransfer, StockMovement, RepairOrder, ProgrammingOrder, InvoiceSequence

### ShopSettings fields
`shopName`, `phone`, `address`, `invoicePrefix`, `logoUrl`, `invoiceFooter`, `invoiceShowBarcode`

### Rules
- Money: `Decimal @db.Decimal(12, 2)` — never Float
- IDs: `cuid()`
- Business dates: `@db.Date`
- Migrations: `prisma migrate deploy` in Docker via `scripts/docker-init.sh`

---

## Inventory & Stock

- **All stock changes MUST use `prisma.$transaction`**
- Sale → decrease qty + log `StockMovement` type `SALE`
- Purchase → increase qty (movement log optional in service)
- Returns → adjust stock + movements
- StockTransfer → TRANSFER_OUT / TRANSFER_IN
- SaleItem stores `costPriceSnapshot` for profit reports
- **Auto SKU:** leave empty on create → `generateUniqueSku()` in `inventory-service.ts`

---

## POS & Sales

### POS (`/pos`)
- Product grid + category tabs + search
- Categories from `Product.category.name` (in-stock products only)
- Arabic category labels: `messages/*/pos.categoryNames`
- Payment: CASH | CARD | ON_ACCOUNT (requires customer)
- On complete → redirect to `/pos/sales/[id]` (invoice + print)

### Sales list (`/sales`)
- Date filter (from/to), today/this week shortcuts
- Shows invoice, customer, line items (name × qty × price), payment, employee
- Links to invoice detail and PDF print

---

## Repairs & Programming

| Module | Path | Model |
|--------|------|-------|
| Repairs | `/repairs` | `RepairOrder` |
| Programming | `/programming` | `ProgrammingOrder` |

Both: form + table + status workflow (NEW → IN_PROGRESS → READY → DELIVERED).

Programming orders are **separate** from selling Programming-category products via POS.

---

## Branding

- **Shop name** from `ShopSettings.shopName` — passed to Sidebar/Header via dashboard layout
- **Logo** uploaded to `public/uploads/` (gitignored except `.gitkeep`)
- **Invoice PDF** uses shop settings + Noto Sans Arabic (`lib/pdf/register-fonts.ts`)
- Do NOT hardcode shop name in sidebar — read from settings

---

## Money Display

`formatMoney()` in `lib/utils.ts`:
- No trailing `.00` for whole numbers
- Latin digits (`numberingSystem: "latn"`)
- Use everywhere in UI; PDF uses same helper

---

## Profit Formulas

```
GrossProfit = Σ(saleItems: (unitPrice - costPriceSnapshot) × qty) − returns
NetProfit   = GrossProfit − Σ(expenses)
```

`lib/domain/profit.ts`, `lib/application/services/report-service.ts`

