## Production & Docker

### Quick start

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Set: AUTH_SECRET, AUTH_URL, ADMIN_EMAIL, ADMIN_PASSWORD

docker compose up -d --build
```

Open `http://localhost:APP_PORT` (default **3022**).

### Services (`docker-compose.yml`)

| Service | Role |
|---------|------|
| `postgres` | PostgreSQL 16 — data in `postgres_data` volume |
| `migrate` | `scripts/docker-init.sh` → migrate + bootstrap admin if empty DB |
| `app` | Next.js production on port 3000 → mapped to `APP_PORT` |
| `seed` | Demo data — **profile `demo` only**, not started by default |

### Demo / seed data

```bash
# After app is running (Docker)
docker compose --profile demo run --rm seed
npm run docker:seed

# Local dev (requires DATABASE_URL)
npm run db:seed
```

Seed: Arabic products, ~800+ sales (180 days), customers, repairs, programming.  
Does **not** delete users. Demo employee: `employee@demo.shop` / `employee123`

### Useful commands

```bash
docker compose down          # stop (keep data)
docker compose down -v       # stop + wipe database
docker compose logs -f app   # app logs
npm run docker:up            # up -d --build
npm run docker:down
npm run docker:logs
```

### Rules

- `AUTH_URL` must match browser URL exactly
- `AUTH_SECRET`: `openssl rand -base64 32`
- Bootstrap admin from `.env` on first empty DB
- **`public/` MUST exist** for Docker build

### Local dev
```bash
npm run dev:kill
npm run dev:clean -- --port 3002
```
Uses `--webpack` (not Turbopack) to avoid cache issues.

